Product Data Overview
Data Categories:
Product Category, Sales, Profit: General order details.
Returns: Information about returned orders, with columns:
Returned: Indicates if an order was returned.
Order ID: Unique identifier for each order.

Date Dimension (DimDate):
A table created for time-based analysis, covering all transaction dates.

Key Metrics (DAX Measures):
New Customers by Year: Tracks first-time customers each year.
Year-over-Year (YoY) Sales Growth: Compares sales performance to the previous year.
Customer Lifetime Value (CLV): Calculates total sales per customer over time.
RFM Scoring: Ranks customers based on:
Recency: Last purchase date.
Frequency: Number of purchases.
Monetary: Total spending.
Returned Orders Count: Counts how many orders were returned.

How to Use the Dashboard:
Open the Power BI file.
Use slicers to filter data by year, region, or product category.
Hover over visuals for detailed insights.
Check the map visualization for geographic customer distribution.

Setup Steps:
Import dataset files (Orders.csv, Returns.csv) into Power BI.
Create a DimDate table for all transaction dates.
Load the dataset and refresh the model.

Future Enhancements:
Add Churn Rate Analysis to monitor customer retention.
Include more KPIs, such as Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC).
Enable real-time data updates.
